        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 2 at 1:16AM CDT until August 2 at 1:45AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 116 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Lake Fort
Phantom Hill, or near Nugent, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Northeastern Abilene, Nugent, and Hamby around 120 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Hodges,
Funston, Mccarty Lake, Big Country Baptist Assembly, Lake Fort
Phantom Hill, Us-283 Near The Callahan-
Shackelford County Line, and The Intersection Of Us-
180 And Farm Road 600.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
